# Desktop Application Guidelines

## Architecture Overview

### Main Process
The desktop application is built with Electron and follows a main process/renderer process architecture. The main process code is located in [apps/desktop/electron/](mdc:apps/desktop/electron).

Key files:
- [main.ts](mdc:apps/desktop/electron/main.ts) - Main process entry point
- [preload.ts](mdc:apps/desktop/electron/preload.ts) - Preload script for secure IPC
- [protocol-handler.ts](mdc:apps/desktop/electron/protocol-handler.ts) - Custom protocol handling
- [updater.ts](mdc:apps/desktop/electron/updater.ts) - Auto-update functionality

### Process Communication
The application uses IPC (Inter-Process Communication) for communication between main and renderer processes:

```typescript
// Main Process (main.ts)
ipcMain.handle('channel-name', async (event, args) => {
  // Handle the request
  return result;
});

// Renderer Process (preload.ts)
contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('eidos', {
  invoke(channel: string, ...args: any[]) {
    return ipcRenderer.invoke(channel, ...args);
  }
});
```

